abstract: French judge rules order to evacuate bustling Calais refugee camp known as 'the Jungle' will not require closing of school, theater, restaurant and other impromptu institutions which emerged to serve thousands of migrants; ruling, which placated both French officials and migrants and their supporters, leaves fate of camp unclear.
lead_paragraph: The French government got permission to relocate some of the migrants, but for now, anyway, the camp cannot be leveled, a court ruled.

headline.main: Some Calais ‘Jungle’ Camp Migrants Get Eviction Reprieve
headline.print_headline: Migrant Camp’s Busy Life Goes On as Evictions Loom
